  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nWe use the Besu node, and during the process we understood that the gas price is calculated wrongly.\r\nThe OpenEthereumâ€™s value is changing from block to block, but for Besu it is the same.\r\nMethod that we use: `eth_gasPrice`\r\nCan you please check, if everything works correct?\r\n\r\nRequest:\r\n```\r\n{\r\n    \"id\": \"blockNumber\",\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"method\": \"eth_gasPrice\",\r\n    \"params\": []\r\n}\r\n```\r\nResponse(OpenEthereum):\r\n```\r\nResponse:\r\n{\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"result\": \"0xcce416600\",\r\n    \"id\": \"blockNumber\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\nResponse(Besu):\r\n```\r\nResponse\r\n{\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"id\": \"blockNumber\",\r\n    \"result\": \"0x3e8\"\r\n}\r\n\r\n```",
