    "body": "@wetryingtodorock thanks for raising this! Indeed, [the JSON RPC spec](https://eth.wiki/json-rpc/API#eth_gasPrice) is quite vague about this call: \r\n> Returns the current price per gas in wei.\r\n\r\nWe currently interpret that as returning the minimum gas price allowed on the network (set by the [`min-gas-price` flag](https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/Reference/CLI/CLI-Syntax/#min-gas-price)). It seems that OE and Geth use the median/average gas price over a range of previous blocks, which produces some ok but not great estimates \r\n(see[ this Geth issue](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/15825), for example). \r\n\r\nIs this what you would like to see from the endpoint? If you have any specific requirements, we'd love to hear them and are open to adapting the endpoint. ",
