    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@shemnon Personally, I'd prefer the default to be 100 blocks and 50% if pulling 100 blocks of data wouldn't affect the performance (basically the more blocks are considered the better?). Another thing to note is that on chains such as Ethereum Classic, a lot of blocks are empty. So maybe it would make sense to only consider the last X blocks that actually have some transactions in there? With that said, I have no idea how Geth and OpenEthereum handle empty blocks in this case. It could also simply fallback to the configured minimum if all last X blocks are empty for simplicity. ",
