    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If there are a lot of empty blocks I don't think transaction inclusion will be a big issue.  \r\n\r\nThe downside of too much of a windows is (a) performance and (b) it hides local spikes.  I think 100 blocks (~20 minutes) is about as far back as one would want to go for an on-chain oracle.  Like Tim said 3rd parties are the best because they take into consideration the entire mempool.",
